  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for libssh",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for libssh fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2025-8277: memory exhaustion leading to client-side DoS due to improper memory management when KEX process is\n  repeated with incorrect guesses (bsc#1249375).\n- CVE-2025-8114: NULL pointer dereference when an allocation error happens during the calculation of the KEX session ID\n  (bsc#1246974).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
